  "plot_summary": "[HANG0] * This is the first month in Marvel's history where the upper-left-corner of the various books showed a small figure of the book's main character (or later characters plural).&nbsp; Legend has it that it was Steve Ditko's idea and that when Stan Lee saw it, he liked it so much, he ordered it used on all Marvel titles from that point on.&nbsp; (The letters page of FF #18 confirms that it was Ditko's idea, and it's clear there as well that it's well-liked by the fans.)&nbsp; And in fact, there is a full-page notice about it <i>inside </i>of [LINK:1963:ASM_2_asm1|ASM #2] that highlights what to look for - \"the greatest symbols in comics!\"&nbsp; All appearing with the \"Marvel Comics Group\" box next to the 12 cents price.\n\n[HANG0] * The special announcement page of [LINK:1963:FF_14|FF #14] points out that so many requests come in for letters pages in their anthology-style mags (what I call  <i>Journey Into Strange Tales of Suspense to Astonish</i>), but that they don't have time to do it, so they suggest that the FF letters page be the \"melting pot\" for all the mags except <i>Spider-Man</i>, who has his own page already.&nbsp; Interesting letters about Thor, Ant-Man, Human Torch and Iron Man will all appear there for now.\n\n[HANG0] * <i>Sgt. Fury and his Howling Commandos</i> is announced as coming soon in  [LINK:1963:FF_14|FF #14].",
