  "subtitle": "[ASSET: right | LusciousChick | width=12%] This month's VMA goes to [LINK:1963:TTA_43_ant0|TTA #43] for \"Hey guys -- dig the luscious chick!\"\n[BR]\n[BR] (Of course, in this <i>particular</i> case, by the time the \"guys\" turn around, the girl has been hit with an aging ray until she could pass as their <i>mother</i> -- but that's beside the point!)\n\n(Though [LINK:1963:FF_14|FF #14] with two female fan groups fighting over Mr. Fantastic did at least factor into the final ruling with \"Sarge -- <b>help!</b>  I can't hold these nutty females back!\"&nbsp; <i>Hahahaha</i>!)",
  "review_text": "This month featured 7 graded stories over 6 issues (ASM had two) for a weighted average of [SPAN: severity=error; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=x.xx], the exact same poor rating as last month.&nbsp; It is a true testament to how bad comics must have been back then that Marvel was able to survive such a poor showing two months in a row.&nbsp; Of the six published books this month, <i>four</i> of them rated 2.5 or <i>lower</i>, and one other a 3.0.&nbsp; Thank goodness for the <i>Amazing Spider-Man</i>, which so far has been quite good.&nbsp; It is solely responsible for this month grading even as high as it did.\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** SUMMARY_BEGIN ***\n*** THIS MONTH ***4 graded stories over 3 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 2 grade character issue   weight 8.0   asm       ASM #2  0.5 5.0   asm       ASM #2  0.5 3.0   thor      JIM #91 0.5 2.0   ant       TTA #43 0.54.50*** LAST MONTH ***6 graded stories over 6 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 4 grade character issue   weight 7.0   ff        FF #13  1.0 3.5   ant       TTA #42 0.5 3.5   torch     ST #107 0.5 3.0   iron      TOS #40 0.5 1.8   thor      JIM #90 0.5 1.0   hulk      HULK #6 1.03.48\n*** SUMMARY_END ***]",
  "letters_page": "[HANG0] * Introduction of the Vulture and Tinkerer\n[HANG0] * Puppet Master somehow survives (which I'm not sure is as much of a highlight or a misfortune for readers everywhere)\n[HANG0] * Lowlight of the <i>year</i> so far is the evil Dr. Strange!&nbsp; Who will ever forget this absurdity?\n\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** INTRODUCTION_BEGIN ***\nNotes | first | villain | Sandu\nNotes | first | Valkyries\nNotes | first | villain | Time Master (Elias Weems)\nVulture | villain | Milestone: (first)\nTinkerer | villain | Milestone: (first)\n*** INTRODUCTION_END ***]\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_BEGIN ***]\n[HANG0] * Thor battles a villain so empty the story has to spiral to fill the space.\n[HANG0] * Ant‑Man watches the plot get old faster than the machine ages its targets - a threat that expires almost before it even begins.\n[HANG0] * Spider‑Man's high‑flying puzzle of the month gets solved with deduction, not fists or altitude.\n[HANG0] * FIXME - write something\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_END ***]",
  "ownership": "[HANG0] * Loki is back again\n[HANG0] * The FF face off against a calculating master mind\n[HANG0] * The Human Torch and Iron Man do their normal thing\n[HANG0] * and Ant-Man finds himself a new partner!\n\nBut will it be enough to rescue Marvel from its shoddy beginning of 1963?"
}